              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">Gomphe Baniare</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;09/25/2003&nbsp;: 2:39:21 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">I have a DarkFelt robe for 10% mana pres on nukes anyway, so I just don't find much use in BoT on raids.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br />If I had BoT, I would definately use it whenever I can; especially on raids.  I don't know what mobs you have been raiding or how many people you're taking along to kill a mob, but never underestimate the power of DoT stacking.  Just remember, the longer the fight, the more damage necros can do with minimual amount of mana.  Our offensive spells aren't really designed for the instant kills; it's more designed to kill the mob slowly.<br /><br />Case in point, in the Agnarr guild raid last night with 2 other necros, I refreshed my DoT series (FP, DP, SK, Pryo, Splurt) 8 times during the course of the fight and was still had 40% mana left while the nukers were going OOM.  And when the nukers had to sit to med for mana, I was still doing damages with my DoTs.  You see, when nukers have to med, they don't do damage.  But when necros sit and med, we can still do damage; all we have to do is refresh the DoT every so often.<br /><br />So it all depends on how you wanna look at things.  You wanna whack a mob with a sledge hammer 10 times and then wait several minutes before you can do it another 10 times or would you whack a mob continiously and constantly with a small hammer?<br /><br /></span></font></td>
